sql:
SELECT DISTINCT first_name || ' ' || last_name AS participant_name
FROM participants
ORDER BY participant_name;

SELECT experiment_name
FROM experiments
ORDER BY experiment_name;

SELECT participant_id, reaction_time
FROM participant_metrics
ORDER BY reaction_time ASC;

external_knowledge:
- Faster reaction times indicate better performance; 
- Ranking from fastest to slowest signifies that participants with lower average reaction times are ranked higher; 
- The context of the query implies a competitive or analytical setting where assessing performance based on reaction times is crucial.
